-- U.K. Stocks Pare Losses; Benchmark FTSE 100 Slips 0.1 percent in London
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-10-18T09:32:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/stocks-pare-losses-man-group-lloyds-gain-vedanta-leads-miners-retreat.html
U.K. stocks pared losses, as shares
of Man Group Plc and Lloyds Banking Group Plc offset a retreat
in mining companies.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index slid 0.1 percent to 5,697.16
at 10:27 a.m. in London. The gauge earlier fell as much as 0.6
percent.  Man Group, a hedge-fund manager, increased 2.5 percent to
270.6 pence. Lloyds Banking Group Plc gained 1.9 percent to
71.50 pence.  Vedanta Resources Plc led mining companies lower, falling
2.9 percent to 2,221 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  